Multimix Academy, Nigeria’s leading Supply Chain Management, Logistics, and  Business Process Training Academy, has hosted a roundtable conference with stakeholders in the industry at Radisson Blu, Lagos. The discussion aimed to provide Multimix Academy with the required value to the trade industry and a curriculum review with intense industry participation. Chairman of Multimix Academy and Director General, African Centre for Supply Chain, Dr Obiora Madu, said: “The meeting represent the needs, interests, and learning areas that members of the industry need in the workplace”.   Why we raise funds, Rotary     Media group partners firm     PIA transforming oil and gas growth, says NGA   Multimix Academy, she said, has provided consistent value and proficient industry leadership in the global trade sector in Nigeria. Madu assured participants of the planned execution of their assessments and the influence it will have on the restructuring of the curriculum to meet the current need of the industry. Managing Director of Multimix Academy Oluchi Okafor, said the business environment driven by innovations in technology and knowledge, is the reason for the change of the brand identity.